          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831133?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Various payment methods provide different conveniences, perks and protections from fraud.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: iStock </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001113428"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/imani-moise" itemprop="url" rel="author">Imani Moise</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Aug. 8, 2023 5:30 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/credit-card-payment-app-fraud-security-3188221b"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Buyers have more ways to pay for things than ever before: <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/AAPL" class="company-name">Apple</a> Pay, Venmo, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/credit-card-cost-fees-legislation-8782d2e9?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">credit cards</a> and dozens of other options. What you choose might matter as much as the purchase itself.</p><p> Each of the different payment methods provides various conveniences, perks and protections from fraud. Credit cards have long been the default option of choice. But <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/federal-reserve-raises-interest-rates-to-22-year-high-3c3e499c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">higher interest rates</a> have now raised the cost of carrying a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/credit-card-car-debt-payments-behind-decc1a22?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">credit-card balance</a> .</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/teens-venmo-uber-amazon-accounts-5043f9d2?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Money-transfer apps such as Venmo</a> and Zelle processed nearly $900 billion last year, and the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau expects that number to reach $1.6 trillion by 2027.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> These apps and services provide easy instant payments, usually for free. The downside is that these options offer fewer protections from <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/jpmorgan-other-banks-in-talks-to-reimburse-scammed-zelle-customers-11669608886?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">scams and unfulfilled orders</a> .</p><p> “The US consumer is very driven by convenience. They may not be directly driven by security,” said James Anderson, managing director at Paze, a bank-owned digital wallet.</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/dont-forget-to-block-your-ex-on-your-payment-apps-207358bc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Payment apps</a> are among the fastest-growing sources of fraud reports and losses, according to Federal Trade Commission data. Overall fraud losses have increased more than fivefold to $1.2 trillion since 2019. Losses tied to payment apps jumped from $5 million to $47 million over the same period, according to the FTC data.</p><p> As new payment options gain acceptance, consumers should try to educate themselves how to use these methods safely, said Seth Ruden, director of global advisory at BioCatch, a fraud-detection software company.</p><p> “The channel itself is not the villain. The bad actors are the scammers, the social engineers and exploit artists,” he said.</p><p> Here&#39;s how to weigh the security, convenience and benefits of each payment option:</p><h3> Credit and debit cards</h3><p> When you swipe or tap your card or authorize a card transaction online, the merchant&#39;s bank communicates with your bank through a card network such as <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MA" class="company-name">Mastercard</a> or <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/V" class="company-name">Visa</a> to ask permission to withdraw a certain amount. Your bank then decides whether to approve the transaction based on your available funds or credit and the likelihood the transaction is fraudulent. If approved, your bank puts a hold on the funds until they are sent to the merchant&#39;s account, usually within a business day.</p><p> Credit cards can be the most rewarding way to pay online. Card issuers use the revenue from transaction fees <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-pandemic-didnt-end-card-rewards-it-made-them-stronger-20fd03c9?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">to fund perks</a> for customers such as cash-back deals, travel points, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-lounge-battle-royale-coming-soon-to-your-airport-b09cf303?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">access to airport lounges</a> and fraud protection.</p><p> A credit card can be expensive if you don&#39;t pay your balance in full, and higher interest rates have now raised the cost of carrying a credit-card balance. Paying off a $1,000 balance in 12 months at the current average annual percentage rate of 22.16% means $103 in interest, compared with $77 roughly a year ago when the average was 16.65%, according to estimates from the Federal Reserve.</p><p> Debit cards don&#39;t offer the same rewards as credit cards since their issuers make less money from each transaction. They do come with similar fraud and payment protections as credit cards. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="468" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-831153?width=700&amp;height=468" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Apps such as Zelle move money more quickly than card payments because the payment is authorized once the sender hits submit.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Tiffany Hagler-Geard/Bloomberg News</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Federal regulations require issuers to reimburse customers for unauthorized transactions of more than $50 and allow customers to dispute charges within 30 days. Many credit cards also provide purchase protection, meaning you can ask for reimbursements directly from your issuer if something you buy is lost, damaged or inconsistent with what was advertised.</p><p> Few people make the most of their credit-card benefits, payments experts said. After finding most people don&#39;t bother to read the fine print when they sign up for a new card, Mastercard is now notifying customers of benefits in real-time.</p><p> “If I have to read a big booklet or call a number to understand what my benefits are, I&#39;m not doing it,” said Chiro Aikat, executive vice president of US market development at Mastercard.</p><h3> Digital wallets</h3><p> Digital wallets such as <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/PYPL" class="company-name">PayPal</a> or Apple Pay are among the safest and easiest ways to pay online. Checking out with a wallet is typically faster than paying with a credit card directly since one doesn&#39;t have to re-enter billing information and shipping address.</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>Which payment method do you favor, and why?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p> All of the protections and benefits associated with the underlying card are still in effect for wallet transactions, so it is best to connect these wallets to a credit card directly to maximize your protection, said Corie Wagner, an analyst at Security.org, a safety-product review site.</p><p> If a digital wallet gives you the option to link a bank account directly, you should read the policy agreement to make sure you understand what is protected. For example, PayPal offers an extra level of purchase protection, but Apple Pay and Google Pay don&#39;t.</p><p> Wallets also offer additional layers of security through encryption and biometric verification and many don&#39;t share sensitive financial data such as your 16-card number with individual merchants. “Use as many authentication factors as possible” such as Face ID or personal identification numbers, Wagner said. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=F5C2DBC2-7CEB-4D03-BA48-E58580F05D20&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fcredit-card-payment-app-fraud-security-3188221b&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Tap-to-pay is growing in the US, thanks in part to its security and ease of use. But it&#39;s more complicated than it looks. WSJ takes you inside one of Square&#39;s card readers to break down the tech that powers contactless payments. Photo illustration: Xingpei Shen<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><h3>Peer-to-peer payment apps</h3><p> Apps such as Venmo, Cash App and Zelle were designed to help people send money to friends and family, but they are now used in more settings. They move money more quickly than card payments because, instead of waiting on banks to approve the transaction, the payment is authorized once the sender hits submit. It is almost impossible to get money back once it has been sent.</p><p> These payment methods aren&#39;t regulated as heavily as cards, so users might still be on the hook for unauthorized payments if a swindler gets control of their accounts.</p><p> “Use it to pay people you know, and trust,” said Meghan Fintland, a Zelle spokeswoman. “They&#39;re not meant to have the credit-card security.”</p><h3> Bank transfers</h3><p> Businesses are increasingly offering ways to pay with your bank account directly since Automated Clearing House, or ACH, transfers are much cheaper to process than cards. This option should only be considered in exchange for a discount, payments executives said.</p><p> Consumers should be selective in sharing their bank information with merchants since wire transfers don&#39;t have the same protection guarantees as cards.</p><p> If a business requests a direct bank transfer instead of a card payment, choosing a slower option over the newer instant methods such as Zelle might be best. ACH transfers typically take a few days to settle, giving you a few more days to try to stop the transaction before the money leaves your account.</p><p> “The slower it is, the greater likelihood is that you&#39;ll be able to get recourse,” Ruden, at BioCatch, said.</p><p> Write to Imani Moise at <a href="mailto:imani.moise@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">imani.moise@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 08 Aug 2023 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/credit-card-payment-app-fraud-security-3188221b</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/credit-card-payment-app-fraud-security-3188221b<author><![CDATA[Imani Moise]]></author><category> WSJ生活工作</category><category>Credit Types/Services</category><category> Credit Cards</category><category> Banking/Credit</category><category>金融服务</category><category>Financial Technology</category><category> Mobile Payment Systems</category><category> Electronic Payment Systems</category><category> Technology</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>Fraud</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>fraud</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>credit types</category><category>服务</category><category>credit cards</category><category> banking</category><category> credit</category><category>金融服务</category><category>financial technology</category><category> mobile payment systems</category><category> electronic payment systems</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘First to the Front’ Review: A Leading Lady of Journalism]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>一位编辑给她贴上了“刺刀边境通讯员”的标签，因为她通常是最先到达战区的人之一。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12770427345856314244904590126000121988496"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830547?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 1955 年，迪基·查佩尔 (Dickey Chapelle) 拍摄海军陆战队照片。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：威斯康星历史学会</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12770427345856314244904590126000121988496"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"><span class="author" itemprop="name">夏洛特·格雷</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 7 日下午 5:58 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/first-to-the-front-review-a-leading-lady-of-journalism-abe61786"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>迪基·查佩尔的一生读起来就像一部好莱坞电影。一位戴着珍珠耳环的摄影记者和战地记者打破了所有刻板印象，打破了故事并超越了美国海军陆战队的勇敢；她受到自由战士的尊敬，受到五角大楼高层的咨询，并在退休担任名誉教授之前被授予总统自由勋章。</p><p>这一切都发生在真正的迪基·查佩尔身上——1918 年出生于密尔沃基，原名乔吉特·迈耶——除了自由勋章和教授职位。相反，查佩尔于 1965 年在越南随海军陆战队排巡逻时被杀，很快就被人们遗忘了。她的许多报告和快讯从未付诸出版，要么是因为她找不到新闻媒体，要么是因为审查制度压制了它们。她爱国、有原则、坚韧到鲁莽的地步。正如洛里莎·莱因哈特（Lorissa Rinehart）在《率先上前线》中所描述的那样，查佩尔坚持用自己的眼睛看每个故事，从士兵而不是将军的角度来描述事件。 “按理说，”莱因哈特女士写道，“迪基·查佩尔应该是一个家喻户晓的名字。” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/schemas/9ff4b76d-bdcb-46cd-935f-e30ea391114c.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p>查佩尔从小就痴迷于飞行的刺激，她是 1934 年被麻省理工学院航空工程班录取的三名女性之一。她很聪明，但更重要的是，她勇敢无畏。因考试不及格而退学后（她更喜欢看飞机而不是设计飞机），她在当地的一个空中马戏团工作，这样她就可以参加飞行课程。她很快意识到有关航展的文章有市场，在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NYT" class="company-name">《纽约时报》</a>刊登了她的一篇报道后，霍华德·休斯的横贯大陆和西部航空（后来的环球航空）的宣传主管为她提供了一份助理的工作。</p><p> 1939 年欧洲爆发战争时，莱因哈特女士告诉我们，“她看到世界在历史时刻的悬崖上摇摇欲坠，并且知道她必须成为其中的一部分。”她的志向是成为一名摄影记者，因此她报名参加环球航空公司的宣传摄影师课程。安东尼·查佩尔（Anthony Chapelle）年龄是她的两倍，很有魅力，善于交际，是一位好老师，迪基爱上了他。两人于1940年结婚。</p><p>迪基·查佩尔 (Dickey Chapelle) 第一次有机会报道军事演习是在 1942 年，当时《Look》杂志派她去拍摄第 14 步兵团在巴拿马丛林中的训练。她证明了自己和学员一样坚韧和勇敢，扛着自己沉重的摄影设备穿过令人窒息的潮湿和蚊子密布的环境。但国内的军事审查机构阻止她的照片出现在印刷品上，理由是这些照片对国家安全构成威胁。</p><p>她的下一次前线机会是 1945 年，当时她收到了前往太平洋战区的委托和官方许可。在那之前，还没有女性摄影师被允许进入战区；她首先加入了海军护理队，负责将伤员疏散到美国医院。她很快就挤到珍珠港，然后到达硫磺岛，在那里她在战斗中掩护海军陆战队。当她拍摄伤员被装上医院船并将镜头对准那些流血过多而死的年轻人时，她磨练了将他们的故事编织成扣人心弦的故事所需的技巧和钢铁般的超然态度。</p><p>到现在为止，查佩尔已经彻底迷上了战争报道。她的报道重点关注生活被战争摧残的士兵、水手、护士、飞行员、游击队员和难民。她告诉她的军事护送人员，她的任务之一就是向家乡传达献血的重要性。正如莱因哈特女士所说，这立即让她受到了所有人的喜爱，“从最闪亮的黄铜纽扣到最肮脏的靴子”。然而，尽管她被命令留在医院船上，但她成功捕捉到了这一动作，导致她的记者证被撤销。她的作品很少出版。</p><p>战后，她说服贵格会派她去东欧进行一次长途旅行，拍摄因战争及其后果（饥饿、无家可归、疾病）而遭受创伤的家庭，特别是儿童。几年之内，《国家地理》等著名出版物就开始使用她的照片和故事。 1956 年，在报道匈牙利革命时，她被捕并入狱六周，其中五周被单独监禁。莱因哈特女士写道，这段经历让她在心理上受到了伤害，并将她对极权主义政权的敌意转变为“击退共产主义浪潮”并讲述“其他人为自由而奋斗的故事”的强烈决心。</p><p>查佩尔的使命将导致她与阿尔及利亚叛乱分子一起参与反对法国统治的斗争，并与菲德尔·卡斯特罗一起</p>古巴革命时期的游击队。一位编辑给她贴上了“刺刀边境通讯员”的标签，因为她通常是第一批到达前线的人。 1961 年，她开始报道美国军队击退越共的努力。 1965 年她去世时，她对美国军事领导人无法理解游击战以及中央情报局在非法扩大战争中的共谋感到愤怒。但军事审查制度阻止她报道她的愤怒。 “也许迪基应该知道她即将走进美国历史上最黑暗的时期之一，”莱因哈特女士写道。但她无法回头，因为“她自己的天真、恐惧或渴望相信美国仍然可以成为自由的灯塔”。<p></p><p> 《先锋》讲述了一个非凡的故事，充满戏剧性和许多可怕的细节。由于没有脚注，很难判断其中许多细节的来源。相反，作者列出了每一章的主要来源，几乎所有这些都是查佩尔自己的笔记、信件、文章和她的自传（最初的标题是“女人在这里做什么？”）。因此，这个故事几乎完全是从查佩尔的角度来讲述的，（大概）是作者的华丽色彩，但没有来自查佩尔的编辑、同行或联系人的评论——他们无疑钦佩她的作品，但可能被她的冒险欲望所激怒。和她的传教士热情。然而，对于那些成为她报道焦点的人来说，迪基·查佩尔始终是一位英雄。她在密尔沃基举行的葬礼是美国女记者首次在战斗中身亡，一名海军陆战队仪仗队盛装出席。</p><p><em>格雷女士是《热情的母亲，强大的儿子：珍妮·杰罗姆·丘吉尔和萨拉·德拉诺·罗斯福的一生》一书的作者，该书将于 9 月出版。</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 21:58:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/first-to-the-front-review-a-leading-lady-of-journalism-abe61786</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/first-to-the-front-review-a-leading-lady-of-journalism-abe61786<category>艺术</category><category>Books</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>摄影</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>观点</category><category>艺术</category><category>books</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>摄影</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>观点</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Chrome Dreams’ by Neil Young Review: From Bootleg to Banner Release]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>这位音乐家的新专辑是一张在 70 年代录制发行但后来被放弃的合集，巩固了他在该十年最佳创作歌手中的地位。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="SB12165777042486313942804590136211558677190"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830590?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">尼尔·杨</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：丹尼·克林奇</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="SB12165777042486313942804590136211558677190"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"><span class="author" itemprop="name">马克·理查森</span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 8 月 7 日下午 5:50 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chrome-dreams-by-neil-young-review-from-bootleg-to-banner-release-47e258ce"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>某种类型的音乐痴迷者——比如那些不断进入前五名名单并在 2000 年电影《高保真》中的角色中认出自己的人——喜欢争论特定十年中最好的乐队或表演。 60 年代的披头士是常见的选择，80 年代的 Prince 也是如此。在 70 年代，也就是黑胶唱片时代的鼎盛时期，竞争尤其激烈，当时音乐处于流行文化对话的中心。史蒂夫·旺德？绝佳的选择，可能是最合乎逻辑的。大卫·鲍伊 ？这也是合理的，特别是考虑到他的地位在过去 15 年里不断增长。或者 Led Zeppelin 乐队，一支改变了硬摇滚声音的乐队？或者甚至是灵魂乐歌手艾尔·格林（Al Green），一位一致性大师，他在这十年的前七张专辑中几乎没有一首弱歌？但我们还必须考虑尼尔·杨。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="639" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-830580?width=639&amp;height=639" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"></figcaption></figure></div><p>在那十年里，这位加拿大创作型歌手发行了八张录音室专辑，并与斯蒂芬·斯蒂尔斯 (Stephen Stills) 合作发行了另一张录音室唱片。他与 Crosby、Stills 和 Nash 一起录制；他发行了一张现场专辑“Time Fades Away”（1973），其中充满了全新的歌曲，其中许多歌曲都很精彩，而另一张“Live Rust”（1979）则被认为是有史以来最好的音乐会摇滚专辑之一制成。纯粹根据当时的作品来看，这是十年来令人印象深刻的作品，足以让杨先生竞选 70 年代最重要的艺术家。但这些官方发布的消息并不是故事的全部。</p><p> Young 先生在 70 年代不断录音，并根据本能做出决定，在最后一刻取消项目，原因只有他自己知道。这一时期的几张黑胶唱片准备发行，然后就被放弃了，对于铁杆粉丝来说，这些默默无闻的唱片已成为传奇。在过去的几年里，作为尼尔杨档案项目的一部分，杨先生发行了几张这样的“丢失的专辑”。其中最新的《Chrome Dreams》（Reprise）于周五推出，最初考虑于 1977 年发行，后来被盗版。这是一本非常棒的歌曲集，如果以这种形式发行，将会被认为是杨先生目录中的上层歌曲。</p><p>多年来，“Chrome Dreams”中的所有歌曲最终都以这样或那样的形式问世。有些被重新录制或配音以供以后发行，而另一些则以与以后发行的形式相同的形式出现在此处。唱片最早的部分有着最熟悉的标题，但“Chrome Dreams”的顺序让它们听起来很新鲜。该专辑以“Pocahontas”开场，这首歌后来成为“Rust Never Sleeps”的亮点，并被评为杨先生职业生涯中最美丽的歌曲。在“Rust”中，这首歌沐浴在混响中，伴随着和声和音效的光环。这与此处找到的杨先生的声音和吉他的录音相同，但有额外的制作。在《Chrome Dreams》的原始录音中，这种赤裸裸的风格给这首歌增添了额外的孤独和忧郁感。</p><p>接下来是安静的“爱的意志”，它几乎不超过耳语；然后是忧郁的“伯利恒之星”，它让人想起杨先生70年代初期作品中乡村风格的节奏，为异常柔和的开场三联画画上了圆满的句号。这种遐想被八分钟的“Like a Hurricane”打断，这是一首中速摇滚歌曲，旨在展示 Young 先生嘈杂而棘手的电吉他主音。这三首歌以不同的顺序打开了杨先生的《American Stars &#39;n Bars》的第二面，这张专辑是他发行的，而不是《Chrome Dreams》，但在开场《Pocahontas》之后听到它们提升了材料，推动可见杨先生在这个时代的歌曲创作有多么强大。</p><p>唱片的后半段从具有古老民谣味道的《肯尼迪船长》开始，后来收录在《鹰与鸽子》（1980）中；华丽的钢琴民谣“Stringman”直到 1993 年才发行，当时 Young 先生发行了他的“MTV Unplugged”表演录音；到“Sedan Delivery”的慢速蓝调版本，该版本出现在“Rust Never Sleeps”的另一张录音中。最后一首之前从未发行过的歌曲的风格更加沉重，带有原始的吉他连复段，让人想起 Link Wray 的“Rumble”。 “Powderfinger”是另一首出现在“Rust”中全乐队改编的歌曲，是 Young 的独奏。虽然它没有其他版本的招摇，但它将杨先生可爱的旋律置于前台，产生了令人心酸的效果。</p><p>尽管杨先生是摇滚史上最敏锐的词曲作者之一，但他也是一位拼贴艺术家，通过以特定并置的方式组合作品来制作精彩的专辑。 “从来没有人提到过我们正在制作一张专辑，”杨先生的伴奏乐队 Crazy Horse 的吉他手弗兰克·桑佩德罗 (Frank Sampedro) 谈到这一时期时说道。 “我们只是演奏和录音。”如果 Young 先生在 1977 年按此顺序发行这些歌曲，会对他的职业生涯产生影响吗？这很难说，但一张如此强大的唱片被搁置，然后被拆成碎片，这一事实充分说明了杨先生在那些令人兴奋的日子里有多少想法。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> -先生。理查森是《华尔街日报》的摇滚和流行音乐评论家。在 Twitter 上关注他@MarkRichardson。</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 07 Aug 2023 21:50:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/chrome-dreams-by-neil-young-review-from-bootleg-to-banner-release-47e258ce</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/chrome-dreams-by-neil-young-review-from-bootleg-to-banner-release-47e258ce<category>艺术评论</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>音乐会</category><category>艺术/娱乐</category><category>音乐</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category><category>艺术回顾</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>音乐会</category><category>艺术</category><category>娱乐</category><category>音乐</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>c&amp;e 排除过滤器</category><category>评论</category></item></channel></rss>